##Five Wuhan Restaurateurs keep diaries as city closes for 20 days

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

The war and epidemic plan for Innovative Economy, a special column launched by Finance and Economics during the new type of pneumonia epidemic, focuses on the new difficulties encountered by enterprises of Innovative Economy and discusses the new countermeasures that should be adopted, hope to be able to help small and medium-sized enterprises together to overcome challenges and seize opportunities. This is the seventh issue. Read the first 6 articles, please Click "which industries are bucking the trend? " "SME Survival Guide" "the almost-collapsed fresh e-commerce stand up again" "Valentine's Day file, also gone" "offline education press the "pause button" "15 days of Tourism" .

Author | Yu Fan

Editor | Wei Jia

The COVID-19 outbreak has led the restaurant industry into the dark.

The latest data released by the Evergrande Research Institute shows that the epidemic has hit the catering, tourism, film and Training Industries Hardest, with retail sales in the catering industry expected to lose 500 billion yuan in just seven days in 2020.

Large restaurants such as Haidilao, Xibei, Grandma's home and Dongpo in Meizhou can last for a long time, and they will also have advantages of scale after the epidemic. However, the catering industry is dominated by small and micro enterprises, most of which are short of funds, weak risk tolerance.

As of today (February 12) , Wuhan has been "closed" for 20 days. CAIJING interviewed the founders of five small and medium-sized restaurant brands in Wuhan, many of whom have been in the restaurant business for 10 years, their enterprises are also at the peak of funds shortage due to the payment of suppliers and the early purchase of ingredients for the Spring Festival peak season, and bear the idle costs such as staff salaries and rent, it also has to survive longer offline shutdowns than its peers in other regions, closed takeout, and the long tail of unpredictable follow-on effects.

Most respondents said cash flows would last at most another three months or so. If not, they will consider closing some stores, reducing business area, adjusting the kitchen operation mode, expanding the proportion of takeout, reducing expenses, to pay only basic wages and other means of self-help. In the future, they are also prepared to apply for bank loans, the sale of housing to obtain more funds.

In the whirlpool, they also convey a different point of view.

Some people promised that they would not lay off workers during the outbreak and agreed that "no one should be fat" during the period. Others donated food, labor and funds when supplies were already scarce, deliver meals to health care workers every day. They are in Wuhan, where the cost of every trip is prohibitive, but they are either looking for food or on their way to it every day.

In addition to the whirlpool, the prevention and control of the pneumonia epidemic has entered the second stage. Many owners of large restaurants have spoken out through the media, hoping to introduce relevant policies to help industries seriously affected by the epidemic, some have already found ways to "share employees" to help themselves, and they are also looking forward to Wuhan's tax, Social Security and loan policies to give everyone a break, but they are more concerned about when the epidemic will end, until then, they are not in the mood to plan for the future of their business.

Life is bigger than anything. Often, they say, it is not the disaster itself that crushes a business, but the people. If the virus kills love, it's something much worse.

Jiqing street after the city closure in Wuhan

Source / interviewees

The end of the epidemic is just the beginning

A cascade of reactions will follow

Lu Huatao, founder of Niangjafu

We have three directly operated stores in Wuhan, with a normal turnover of 60,000 a day, and now all the stores are closed, which can not generate any income; during the Spring Festival, we have a 10-day reserve of food materials, about 200,000, because of the closure of the city, 30 to 40 employees are stuck in dormitories, they can't buy food, they're giving it to their employees, and they're making between 360,000 and 380,000 a month, which is a million-dollar loss for the company, which is basically running out of food.

Hubei Province stipulates that all kinds of enterprises can resume work no earlier than 24:00 on February 13. If the shopping mall in Wuhan asks the restaurant to open on the 14th, then I can only borrow money to buy goods, otherwise I can only default. According to the current situation of the epidemic, it is initially estimated that the epidemic will last until the end of May, and the dark cloud of the epidemic will not pass in a short period of time. Employees will not come, and customers will not go to the shops to spend money, i estimate that the daily turnover in March and April will be at most 10-20% of what it used to be. Even paying utilities will be a problem, not to mention staff salaries and rent.

I started my business in 2009, and this year has been eleven years. According to my experience, opening a store at that time will mean losing money, so why do we still have to open it? To do business, is to keep the losses to a minimum. We can't survive, so we have to close it all, one store at the most.

Looking back on more than 10 years of reading, foreign enterprises work for 10 years, 10 years of entrepreneurship, this thirty, deep feelings. In 2003, I bought 12 apartments in Guangzhou, the early start-up, each store in Wuhan to sell a house, the peak period there are 30 shops. But the business landscape has changed so quickly over the years that if I hadn't sold my house and started a business, I would have had a lot of assets, and now I look back and see nothing, just like a dream.

Catering personnel, rental costs have reached the limit, I opened a shop in Wuhan this decade, the rent has never gone up, not down. We know it's hard for homeowners, but real estate is a long-term investment, and losses on businesses can be converted into 40-year equity terms, while dining is a short-term activity, and losses can be converted into three to five years. One store in Guanggu with a monthly turnover of 1.3 million has been closed due to high rents, four stores have been closed due to the construction of the subway cut-off road, which has greatly affected their revenue, and two other stores have been closed due to the absence of P2P owners and other reasons.

In 2019, the catering industry labor costs as high as 24%-25% , 22% above the red line of two points, is extremely dangerous, profit margin as low as 5%-8% , even the bank's loan interest may not even.

If the rent is high, then my store can only improve efficiency, adjust the operation mode of the kitchen, simplify the menu, compress the area, increase turnover rate, expand the proportion of takeout. We didn't expect to make any money at first, because for a long time, most people were afraid to eat out, so we picked up the meals first, sent the staff out to deliver the food, and got things rolling.

And reduce the company's expenses. I will talk to the staff, can accept the basic salary, can not accept can only leave; first suspended two months of social security, such as the flow of funds to make up. Now the staff in the dormitory is also very anxious, they need money, but the company can not send, they do not know the store will be what, do not see relatives, also can not go home.

More than 200,000 catering enterprises in Hubei, in fact, everyone is in a similar situation right now. They are all very anxious. They do not know when the epidemic will end, and even if the epidemic ends, it is only the beginning, a chain reaction will follow: The supplier will ask for last month's payment, everyone will be very difficult and may have to go to court; the employee will ask for a subsidy, or let him resign after paying a month or two of salary, if you do not pay, you may have to deal with Labor Arbitration; how to repay the loan on hand, if the country does not give interest-free loans to do. Even if the outbreak ends, just the static problems of the caterer end, dynamic problems will follow.

I'M GONNA keep the House. I'm GONNA do it

Nine years of branding and employees working side by side

Li Bojia, founder of rice cookers

We are a fast food chain, in Wuhan, there are 10 stores, one of which is ready to decorate, would like to put forth all efforts in 2020 big fight, did not expect to encounter such havoc.

During the Spring Festival period, we planned 3 stores to open normally. Since Academician Zhong Nanshan said "the virus can spread from person to person" , we went one by one with the stores to apply for closing the stores. Only after we had written the application report did the stores agree. After we closed for a day or two, all the stores were closed.

Normally, from the opening of the fifth day of the first month to the Lantern Festival, all the stores had a total of 1.4 million running water, but the outbreak occurred without any cash flow, and was responsible for the salaries of 98 employees and the rent of 10 stores, very embarrassed. 80% of our staff come from Hubei Province outside Wuhan, from a good point of view, we close the shop promptly, did not affect the staff, at present everyone is safe, not a family infected with the virus.

I have always stressed in the work group, Safety First, charging second, with the family third, let everyone report daily physical condition, management regularly live online training, organized book club, with everyone to do some small games. Because there are 10 people in Wuhan, I will also talk to the staff, especially some young people for psychological counseling. We agreed that no one would get fat, and even though we were catering, we were running low on supplies, so we had to be frugal.

Of course, the staff is most concerned about the next arrangements, I told them: during the epidemic will not lay off staff, but also hope that the staff and we stand on the line, we consult with the staff, from the holiday after the minimum wage calculation. When I said this, all the employees accepted it, even many offered to give up their February salary, while some executives offered to accompany the company through the epidemic without paying a penny. In addition, several years of cooperation landlord contact me, free rent in February. All this has been a great inspiration to me.

It is often not the disaster itself that overwhelms a business, but the people. Now that we're shut down, there's only so much we can do, but as long as people stay focused, we can put everything back together again.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I recently read Yoshinoya's business of adversity, and in the history of modern Japanese restaurant chains, no Japanese company, other than the Yoshino family, has survived two major crises in thirty or three years, even if a day closed, can ensure that the normal payment of wages for all employees, lasting two years.

With reference to the SARS epidemic, it will take at least three to four months for the restaurant industry to recover, and at least another quarter for the public to recover. And even if it does open, I expect at least a 30% drop in sales, which may require an increase in takeout or group meals. We always pay attention to the experience of the canteen, not too enlarged take-away, not to rely on the volume of take-away, take-away food, previously the ratio of 7:3. But after the outbreak, the ratio would objectively be reversed, if not adjusted.

I also prepared for the worst, and my wife agreed to sell the house to rent, but also to keep the brand for nine years and work side by side with the staff.

All restaurants in Wuhan are now closed, and some chains with central kitchens or large food processing plants are still serving free meals for hospitals. They can at least do their part. We, who don't have a central kitchen, have smaller stores, and though we have 800,000 to 1 million ingredients in stock before the Spring Festival, all of them are stored in a central warehouse on the outskirts of Huangpi District, which can not be brought in after the city is closed, there's nothing I can do to help.

However, I believe that after the outbreak, the catering industry in Wuhan will upgrade to a higher level and become the national leader. Because Wuhan is the center of the Vortex, everyone will learn from the experience, and our customers will demand more. The future of catering recovery is based on wearing masks, gloves is no longer a show, but the practice of all catering people to put food safety first.

Don't talk about economics in front of life

The founder of Tavern 18, Wang Fan

Our oldest shop opened 10 years, there is a shop in Wuhan Western hot list first, there is a shop on the Wuhan Public Opinion Bar recommended list, is the country's very well-known craft restaurant. In the past three or four years, the parties during the Spring Festival were mostly held in pubs. The number of customers in our shops increased year by year. Due to the epidemic, the four shops that had been scheduled to open during the Spring Festival were closed. On the day of the closure of the city, our shops were fully disinfected.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Full decontamination before closing

We have reserved about 450,000 ingredients and drinks for the Spring Festival. Some of the fresh ingredients and fresh beer have become rations for the staff left behind, and some have been distributed to medical staff. Now during the period of closure, the three stores daily loss of 80-100,000 turnover, and the company's cash flow only two and a half months, if it lasts more than three months, I can only personal loans.

Catering is just one of our sectors. We also have trading companies and beer factories. After the epidemic, catering will certainly slowly recover, the objective of the epidemic will force the growth of catering enterprises, pay more attention to production safety, Shop Operation Safety and transparency, as well as the control of purchase channels. Our trading company is to bars and restaurants, now some individual users and sales contact, asked whether the distribution of beer, but we do not know how to complete a safe enough distribution service, and did not come up with very good standards, so the trading company is on hold.

I am more worried about the brewery, originally planned to launch after the Spring Festival a seasonal cherry beer, this wine production schedule is all done, 100 tons in the brewing pot. But now the biggest worry, on the one hand, is the outside world's concern about the safety of the drinking water and food produced in Wuhan. It is unclear how long it will last, and it is impossible to predict, because the food and beverage industry in the SARS period was 1 / 30th the size it is today, it's nothing compared to today. On the other hand, our customers are all over the country, we don't know when the logistics will resume, the expiration date of craft beer is relatively short, which leads to a bit of confusion in the whole supply chain, and production must be kept on site, i couldn't risk the lives of my staff on duty, so I had to stop them all.

Recently the team is thinking of ways out, we plan to take this batch of wine online platform in the form of a charity sale, donated to the epidemic now affected people, struggling in the front line of medical staff. Now Limited to logistics, we can only be in the form of pre-sale, first to save others, then self-help.

In the old days, when the amount was only a number, for example, it might cost 2 million yuan, there was no deep feeling. However, as the epidemic progressed, all the sectors stopped. When the Balance Day came, we had to calculate the payment owed to the suppliers and the wages to be paid, when the financials sent me the data, it hit me pretty hard.

Wuhan Zhongshan Avenue

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I was born and raised in Wuhan. I went through several stages. The initial stage of the epidemic was confused, followed by panic. Now I am trying to find a way to reconcile with myself. I am trying to figure out how to live my life. We were wondering what we could do for our beloved city? So our staff volunteered to save the 40 cats left behind in Wuhan, and our brewer volunteered to drive the doctor to and from work.

From the beginning of the New Year, my friends and I planned to make a documentary to record the special moments in Wuhan. The main interview target was the "City defenders" of the Empty City, take-out boy, sanitation workers, ordinary police, journalists... when a city is sick, they are still the capillary to provide nutrition, interview on the way, see the empty Jinghan Avenue, Jiqing Street, lingbomen, only heartache. Remember from the 5th day of the city, the riverfront would have only the national day of the lighting project will be lit every night, the riverfront buildings everywhere is "Wuhan refueling. ".

The Moon Lake Bridge after the city closure in Wuhan

But now back to the state of powerlessness, compared to those of us in the center of the Vortex, I think in the field can not go home, the discrimination of Wuhan people more painful. If the virus kills love, it's something much worse. Many voices on the Internet now call attention to the catering industry, attention to small and medium-sized enterprises, the economy is important, but now is not the problem of food, is a matter of life and death, in front of life do not talk about economic issues. When the market economy is oriented, some people may forget their social attributes.

My whole body is in a state of relief

I'm not in the mood to think about saving myself

Lao Wang pork belly chicken hotpot founder, Ye Jinsheng

Lao Wang from the roadside shop, the initial level is not high, later into the business circle, slowly to the high-end walk, to now there are 27 stores in Wuhan, the country has 36.

January and February are the busiest months of the year for pork belly and chicken hotpot. Except for one or two days around the year 30 when business is not very good, the turnover in February is conservatively estimated to be around 11 million, but all of them are now closed for business, it also pays 2 million workers'salaries and 1.9 million yuan in rent.

Hubei regulation of all types of enterprises to resume work as early as 24:00 on February 13, now there are a few shopping malls called me after February 14, I will not open, at least until March 1 to say. Because even if the business, no one dares to go out, the entire city of Wuhan empty. And a lot of employees went home years ago, are in good health, how do I have the heart to let them back to the hard-hit areas. There's nothing we can do. Nothing we can do.

Frankly speaking, the epidemic has not yet stabilized, my whole person is in the state of disaster relief, not in the mood to go back to consider how the enterprise self-help.

Since the New Year's Eve, I and two other bosses of the Guangdong Chamber of Commerce in Hubei Province have not stopped. We were both cooks, so we chipped in, and the next day we started feeding the paramedics. Since we were a hotpot restaurant and couldn't cook Chinese food, we took out all the ingredients from the restaurant's Spring Festival reserve, and another owner made them by hand. So far, we've worked from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. , making and delivering 1,500 meals a day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The meal is on its way to the hospital

When the staff got tired, they joined a volunteer platform and joined seven or eight volunteers to help us pack boxes. After packing, many volunteers with cars were sent directly to Wuhan Tongji Hospital and Wuhan Union Hospital, and the headquarters of Mount Thor and Vulcan Hospital. These workers wear only one mask and take great risks every day.

Through this epidemic, I saw that most restaurant owners in Hubei are very kind, many people donate money, but now the biggest problem is, money is useless. I mobilized Qianji bread students to send 100,000 bread to supplement, and then want to find milk, all the supplies are out of stock. There are still some fresh food that can not be bought at all. I tried every means to contact the owners of various restaurants in Wuhan. If they are willing, they will donate the food. If they are not willing, I will discuss with them whether they can sell it to me. After the seventh day, it is not so difficult to find food, although still closed, but will allow some food into the city.

This period of time, daily contact with the front-line medical staff, I hate the most is his ability, can only do something within the scope of their ability, that can hold on to as long as it.

I don't have much confidence in the delivery business

Li Shuhui, founder of Bonifeng restaurant, Wuhan

From December 30,2019, Wuhan reported the first case of the epidemic began, our company will be based on the experience of SARS, began to arrange for the company to carry out self-protection and restaurant disinfection training. But compared with the previous year's results, all stores saw a 20% decline. I prayed that the outbreak would not spread to Atypical pneumonia, where it had been shut down, but unfortunately, by the time Mr. Zhong Nanshan announced signs of human transmission of the new coronavirus, store sales were down 90 percent, all the 110 tables of New Year's Eve dinner at our old eight-door Chinese restaurant have been canceled. On January 22nd, all the stores were closed. Fortunately, the company's 13 direct stores, more than 200 employees, there was not a case of fever.

The next day, Partner Xiong Fei saw on the Internet that the doctors in the front line only had instant noodles to eat, food security is not guaranteed, so he and his friends started to take out the ingredients from their own library, used to feed the medical staff, many people joined.

But the hardest part of the process is the food and the transportation. We ran out of our own ingredients, we ran out of vegetables, fruits and spices coordinated by the Hubei Cuisine Association, and we spent the next day looking for ingredients. The ingredients from outside could not get into Wuhan, pork and fresh fish are not available in all local supermarkets. In addition, public transport is suspended and employees can not leave or return. Only 10 or more people are involved in hospital feeding. They are now working at high risk every day, during which time the company pays double wages.

These are the things that we can do right now, for as long as we can, and I'm praying every day that we don't have a case on the staff, because if we do, it's not going to happen.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Meal preparation complete

In 2019, only 20 percent of the catering staff could earn money, and the industry was already struggling. Everyone had been looking forward to the Spring Festival very much, and invested all their profits, putting the strength of the staff, food materials and capital reserves in the Spring Festival, no one thought, suddenly under a "snow. ". Our Spring Festival stock of 1 million, 300,000 losses, monthly labor, fixed costs of rent are 1.1 million, the company's cash flow has been cut off.

As far as I can tell, all of our peers have suffered heavy losses, and the larger the enterprise, the greater the losses. Several large-scale Banquets in Wuhan each Spring Festival stock in more than 5 million, the cancellation of more than 1,000 tables, can only be closed, temporary traffic closure, the staff can not go home, all stay in the dormitory daily with snacks instant noodles.

All the upstream suppliers have also suffered heavy losses. In particular, the south China Seafood Market, since January 1, the entire market closed, no goods can be taken out, some seafood owners lost tens of millions, many outlets are self-employed family income source.

I can think of self-help measures are more conventional: to continue negotiations, can reduce part of the rent; then find a loan; in the future in the restaurant's food supply, service more attention to health, because they found out that it's spelled "resistance" to this point.

But I don't have much confidence in the delivery business. The profit margin of the catering industry is only 10% , delivery platform in charge of distribution fees, continue to take 20%-25% , we have no profit, if the future is still such a high discount point, even if do not make money.

Based on what I know so far, it is estimated that the freezing period of Wuhan's catering industry will last at least until May.

In fact, our catering enterprises are now doing public welfare are all fat, we all want to let the epidemic quickly end. Chengdu and Jiangsu have both introduced policies to support small and medium-sized enterprises. Can Wuhan also have corresponding policies on taxes, fees, social security and loans to provide large-scale subsidies to real estate owners, and then through rent-free for more than 3-6 months to the terminal catering enterprises, let everyone take a breath first, the enterprises themselves then find ways to bear the living problems of the employees, no money to pay wages, we send rice and oil will not let the employees go hungry, it is also hoped that the government, when it comes to policy, will give priority to those companies that have contributed to the outbreak and those that have not cut jobs. But we understand that the government has no time for us, after all, to solve the current medical problems.
